<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08419</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REPUBLIC ACT NO. <b>RA11235</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PREVENTING THE USE OF MOTORCYCLES IN THE COMMISSION OF CRIMES THROUGH BIGGER NUMBER PLATES AND IDENTIFICATION MARKS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Preventing The Use Of Motorcycles In The Commission Of Crimes Through Bigger Number Plates And Identification Marks</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates the LTO to maintain a registry of motorcycles in a database to facilitate information retrieval to be used in official investigation and law enforcement purposes and to issue bigger number plates for motorcycles with alphanumeric characters which can be readable from at least twelve (12) meters distance which should be displayed at the back of the motorcycle for the purpose of ensuring the security and safety of citizenry from crimes committed with the use of motorcycles.

Penalizes motorcycle rider and passenger or passengers who used a motorcycle in the commission of a crime, whether grave or less grave felony under the Revised Penal Code, or as a means to escape from the scene of such crime, whether attempted, frustrated, or consummated.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : ‚ÄúMotorcycle Crime Prevention Act.‚Äù</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>YAP, VICTOR A., HERNANDEZ, FERDINAND L., UMALI, REYNALDO V., VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND JR. F., SARMIENTO, CESAR V., ACOP, ROMEO M., NOGRALES, KARLO ALEXEI B., BIAZON, ROZZANO RUFINO B., MARQUEZ, CARLITO S., ABU, RANEO &quot;RANIE&quot; E., MANALO, JESULITO A., PADUANO, JOSEPH STEPHEN S., REVILLA, STRIKE B., PIMENTEL, JOHNNY TY, FARI&Ntilde;AS, RODOLFO C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-10-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Salo (000 2018-11-13)</td><td>2. Alonte (000 2018-11-13)</td><tr><td>3. Garcia (J.E.) (000 2018-11-13)</td><tr><td colspan=3>AUTHORS(Final/Third Reading) :</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>1. Yap (V.)</td><td width='33%'>2. Hernandez (F.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>3. Umali</td><td width='33%'>4. Villafuerte</td><tr><td width='%33'>5. Sarmiento (C.)</td><td width='33%'>6. Acop</td><tr><td width='%33'>7. Nograles (K.A.)</td><td width='33%'>8. Biazon</td><tr><td width='%33'>9. Marquez</td><td width='33%'>10. Abu</td><tr><td width='%33'>11. Manalo</td><td width='33%'>12. Paduano</td><tr><td width='%33'>13. Revilla</td><td width='33%'>14. Pimentel</td><tr><td width='%33'>15. FariÒas</td><td width='33%'>16. Catamco</td><tr><td width='%33'>17. Villarica</td><td width='33%'>18. Sy-Alvarado</td><tr><td width='%33'>19. Nieto</td><td width='33%'>20. Cueva</td><tr><td width='%33'>21. Tambunting</td><tr><td colspan=3>COUNTERPART HOUSE BILL/CONCURRENT RESOLUTION: SB01397</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITTEE REPORT NO.&nbsp00893</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED ON 2018-10-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED BY:&nbspTRANSPORTATION, APPROPRIATIONS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>RECOMMENDATIONS:&nbspApproval in substitution of House Bills Numbered 5381, 5714, 5839